default&#xa0;default2.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultToo often the process is hampered by Local Authorities standing in the way.  For example Redcar &amp; Cleveland currently want to charge legal fees for schools converting
default, even if they already buy in to the LA service. They also insist a school must become a cheque-book school for a ‘few months’ before they can become a
defaultn academy. However, they say that
default it takes a year to make the change to become a cheque-book school! Such
default disputes are intended to deter schools from the process.
default&#xa0;default2.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe DfE
default needs to 
defaulthave better data to identify schools which meet the criteria for being granted academy status, or being compelled
default 
defaultto become an academy by being sponsored, or for being a sponsor. C
