default&#xa0;default2.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFor Free Schools it is not adequate that there is a demand, there
default must also be a need demonstrated by either by demographics (too few places) or by failure to provide adequate quality in other schools in the locality. 
defaultThe DfE needs to have the data to substantiate the case. If not, it appears purely an ideological decis
defaultion which undermines schools in the area – thus having the unintended consequence of 
defaultreducing morale and performance in those schools.
default 
defaultIf the latter, there also needs to be a plan to address this – by improving quality to acceptable levels and/or reducing 
defaultplaces at poor quality schools. Establishing a Free School and leaving it to the market condemns a generation of pupils caught in change.
default&#xa0;default2.4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThere needs to be a route by which 
defaultOFSTED can
default inform the DfE where they identify capacity in high performing schools 
default(perhaps through their HMI Good Practise Guides?). It is clear from the HMCI Annual Report released last week that OFSTED have such performance data – LA by LA – thus the DfE could begin to trawl for capacity by starting with OFSTED data.
